S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: AtoN Number
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Identifier from a list of Aids to Navigation publication, such as List of Lights.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Interoperability Identifier
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A common unique identifier for entities which describe a single real-world feature, and which is used to identify instances of the feature in end-user systems where the feature may be included in multiple data product types.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Name
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The individual name of a feature.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Name Usage
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Classification of the type and display level of the name of a feature in an end-user system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Default Name Display
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The name is intended to be displayed when the end-user system is set to the default name/text display setting.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Alternate Name Display
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The name is intended to be displayed when the end-user system is set to an alternate name/text display setting, for example an alternate language.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Year
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A period of one revolution of the earth around the sun.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Warning Type
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The scope of the MSI warning - NAVAREA, sub-area, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Local Navigational Warning
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition:
Message containing urgent information relevant to safe navigation broadcast to ships in a local area, in accordance with the provisions of the International Convention for the Safety of Life at Sea, 1974, as amended.(Adopted from S-53, 2.2.23)
Local warning means a navigational warning which covers inshore waters, often within the limits of jurisdiction of a harbour or port authority. (Adopted from S-53, 2.2.10)

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coastal Navigational Warning
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition:
Message containing urgent information relevant to safe navigation broadcast to ships in a coastal area, in accordance with the provisions of the International Convention for the Safety of Life at Sea, 1974, as amended.
Coastal warning means a navigational warning promulgated as part of a numbered series by a National Coordinator.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sub-Area Navigational Warning
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition:
Message containing urgent information relevant to safe navigation broadcast to ships in a sub-area, in accordance with the provisions of the International Convention for the Safety of Life at Sea, 1974, as amended.
Sub-area warning means a navigational warning or in-force bulletin promulgated as part of a numbered series by a Sub-area Coordinator.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: NAVAREA Navigational Warning
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition:
Message containing urgent information relevant to safe navigation broadcast to ships in a NAVAREA, in accordance with the provisions of the International Convention for the Safety of Life at Sea, 1974, as amended.
NAVAREA warning means a navigational warning promulgated as part of a numbered series by a NAVAREA Coordinator.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: NAVAREA No Warning
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A message that indicates that there are no navigational warnings to be disseminated in the NAVAREA.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sub-Area No Warning
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A message that indicates that there are no navigational warnings to be disseminated in the sub-area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coastal No Warning
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A message that indicates that there are no navigational warnings to be disseminated in the coastal area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Local No Warning
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A message that indicates that there are no navigational warnings to be disseminated in the local area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: NAVAREA In-Force Bulletin
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A list of serial numbers of NAVAREA warnings which are in- force.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sub-Area In-Force Bulletin
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A list of serial numbers of sub-area warnings which are in-force.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Coastal In-Force Bulletin
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A list of serial numbers of coastal warnings which are in- force.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Local In-Force Bulletin
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A list of serial numbers of local warnings which are in- force.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Warning Number
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The consecutive number re-starts each calendar year at 1 (Leading zeros are not mandatory).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Name of Series
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The NAVAREA or METAREA. Example: NAVAREA IV. Distinction: generalArea, locality

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Nationality
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Identifier of membership of a particular nation.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Agency Responsible for Production
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Identifies the agency which produced the data.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Headline
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Words set at the head of a passage or page to introduce or categorize.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Reference
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The file name of an externally referenced text file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: File Locator
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The location of a fragment of text or other information in a support file.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Application schemas must describe how the associated file is identified. The associated file will commonly be named in a file reference co-attribute of the same complex attribute. Each DCEG must specify requirements for the format of the associated file and the semantics of file locator. For example, the value of file locator may be an HTML ID in an HTML file, line number in a text file) or a bookmark in a PDF file.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Locality Identifier
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Globally unique identifier for the area or locality in the MRN format.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Time of Day Start
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The time corresponding to the start of an active period.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The time of day start must be encoded using 2 digits for the hour (hh), 2 digits for the minutes(mm) and 2 digits for the seconds (ss). This conforms to ISO 8601:2004.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Time of Day End
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The time corresponding to the end of an active period.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The time of day end must be encoded using 2 digits for the hour (hh), 2 digits for the minutes(mm) and 2 digits for the seconds (ss). This conforms to ISO 8601:2004.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date Start
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The earliest date on which an object (for example a buoy) will be present.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The Date Start should be encoded using 4 digits for the calendar year (YYYY), 2 digits for the month (MM) (for example April = 04) and 2 digits for the day (DD). When no specific month and/or day is required/known, indication of the month and/or day is omitted, and replaced with dashes (-). When no specific year is required (that is, the event or date range ends at the same time each year) the following two cases may be considered:- same day each year: ----MMDD- same month each year: ----MM--This conforms to ISO 8601: 2004. Date Start indicates the earliest date of an event or the start of a date range. It is used to indicate the start of a fixed date range, the start of a periodic date range, or the deployment or implementation of a feature at a specific date in the future.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Date End
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The latest date on which an object (for example a buoy) will be present.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The Date End should be encoded using 4 digits for the calendar year (YYYY), 2 digits for the month (MM) (for example April = 04) and 2 digits for the day (DD). When no specific month and/or day is required/known, indication of the month and/or day is omitted, and replaced with dashes (-). When no specific year is required (that is, the event or date range ends at the same time each year) the following two cases may be considered:- same day each year: ----MMDD- same month each year: ----MM--This conforms to ISO 8601: 2004. Date End indicates the latest date of an event or the end of a date range. It is used to indicate the end of a fixed date range, the end of a periodic date range, or the removal or cancellation of a feature at a specific date in the future.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Last Notice Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Date of the last notice to mariner, such as was applied to a chart or publication.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Edition Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Date of publishing for example of a publication, chart, or product.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Chart Plan Number
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Plan number when a chart has more than one panel.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Chart Number
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Chart number. Note, can be either paper chart number or ENC file name.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Publication Affected
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Name of affected publication.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: International Chart Affected
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: International paper chart number. (Not used if chartAffected carry an ENC name).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Chart Publication Identifier
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Identifier for the chart or publication (using the MRN format).

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Int Service
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: An indication of an international service, true = yes, false = no.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Cancellation Date
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Date and time of cancelling a notice or warning.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Reference Category
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Category of reference.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Warning Cancellation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Cancellation of warning which is no longer valid.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Warning Reference
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Reference to relevant warning.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: In-Force
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Reference to warnings or notices that are considered in-force.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: No Message On Hand
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: An indication of no active message.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Scale Minimum
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The minimum scale at which the feature may be used for example for ECDIS presentation.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The modulus of the scale is indicated, that is 1:1 250 000 is encoded as 1250000.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Text
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A non-formatted digital text string.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Should be used, for example, to hold the information that is for short cautionary or explanatory notes. Therefore, text populated in text must not exceed 300 characters. Text may be in English, or in a national language. No formatting of text is possible within text. If formatted text, or text strings exceeding 300 characters, is required, then an alternate concept should be used.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Text Offset Bearing
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The angular distance measured from true north that text associated with a feature is positioned from the feature in an end-user system.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Text Offset Distance
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The distance that text associated with a feature is positioned from the feature in an end-user system.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Text Rotation
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: A statement that expresses if text associated with a feature is to be rotated in the ECDIS display or not.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Restriction
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The official legal statute of each kind of restricted area.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Defines the kind of restriction(s), for example, the restriction for 'a game preserve' may be 'entry prohibited', the restriction for an 'anchoring prohibition' is 'anchoring prohibited'. The complete information about the restriction(s), actually held in handbooks or other publications, may be encoded using an Information type.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Entry Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: [1] An area shown on charts within which navigation and/or anchoring is prohibited. [2] In aviation terminology, a specified area within the land areas of a state or territorial waters adjacent thereto over which the flight of aircraft is prohibiÂ­ted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Entry Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A specified area designated by appropriate authority, within which navigation is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Area To Be Avoided
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An IMO declared routeing measure comprising an area within defined limits in which either navigation is particularly hazardous or it is exceptionally important to avoid casualties and which should be avoided by all ships, or certain classes of ships.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Stopping Prohibited
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area in which a vessel is prohibited from stopping.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Speed Restricted
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area within which speed is restricted.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Language
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The method of human communication, either spoken or written, consisting of the use of words in a structured and conventional way.
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:remarks: The language is encoded by a 3 character code following ISO 639-2/T.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Publication Time
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Date and time of publication of the notice or warning.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Navwarn Type Details
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: Detailed type of a warning or hazard.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Acoustic Recorder
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The temporary or permanent installation of an acoustical instrument in the marine environment for the purpose of tracking the behavior of marine mammals or to monitor their ecosystems.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: AIS Temporary Establishment
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A new AIS has been or will be established for a limited period of time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: AIS Transmitter Establishment
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A new AIS site has been or will be established.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: AIS Transmitter Operating Properly
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The terrestrial AIS transmitter is operating as advertised.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: AIS Transmitter Out Of Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The terrestrial AIS transmitter is inoperative due to a technical issue.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: AIS Transmitter Removal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: AIS transmitter has been or will be permanently removed from service.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: AIS Transmitter Temporary Removal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: AIS transmitter has been or will be temporarily removed from service.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: AIS Transmitter Unreliable
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The terrestrial AIS transmitter is unreliable due to a technical issue or maintenance.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: All Aids To Navigation Unreliable
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: All aids to navigation on a structure or in an area are unreliable due to environmental impact, equipment failure, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Anti Pollution Exercise
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A large scale activity where multiple vessels, surveillance aircraft, and shore-based personnel practice a response to the discharge of a pollutant from a ship (or shore) into the marine environment, in order to evaluate the effectiveness of response capability.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Anti Pollution Operation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A real time response by vessels, surveillance aircraft, and shore-based personnel to resolve the discharge of a pollutant from a ship (or shore) into the marine environment.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Aquaculture Site
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The installation of infrastructure at a new location where the farming of fish, shellfish and aquatic plants in fresh or salt water is undertaken; and, failures at these locations where the infrastructure is reported damaged and may be adrift.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: AtoN Operating Properly
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The outage/failure has been corrected and the aids to navigation has resumed normal operation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Audible Signal Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The characteristics of the audible signal (device activated by e.g. sea state or wind, irrespective of visibility) have been or will be changed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Audible Signal Establishment
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A new audible signal (device activated by e.g. sea state or wind, irrespective of visibility) has been or will be established.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Audible Signal Operating Properly
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The audible signal (device activated by e.g. sea state or wind, irrespective of visibility) is operating as advertised.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Audible Signal Out Of Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The audible signal (device activated by e.g. sea state or wind, irrespective of visibility) is inoperative.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Audible Signal Removal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Audible signal (device activated by e.g. sea state or wind, irrespective of visibility) has been or will be permanently removed from service.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Audible Signal Temporary Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The characteristics of the audible signal (device activated by e.g. sea state or wind, irrespective of visibility) have been or will be temporarily changed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Audible Signal Temporary Establishment
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A new audible signal has been or will be established for a limited period of time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Audible Signal Temporary Removal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Audible signal (device activated by e.g. sea state or wind, irrespective of visibility) has been or will be temporarily removed from service.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Authorized Ice Routeing Information
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Ice routeing information provided by a recognized authority.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Beacon Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The characteristics of the beacon have been or will be changed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Beacon Damaged
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The beacon has sustained damage due to external factors (wind, sea state, collision with a vessel).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Beacon Daymark Unreliable
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Colour of the beacon daymark is not visible due to damage or fading of colours (out of tolerance with colour recommendations).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Beacon Establishment
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A new beacon has been or will be established.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Beacon Missing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: No beacon at the advertised position.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Beacon Removal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Beacon has been or will be permanently removed from service.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Beacon Restored To Normal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The beacon has been restored to normal condition.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Beacon Temporary Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The characteristics of the beacon have been or will be temporarily changed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Beacon Temporary Establishment
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A new beacon has been or will be established for a limited period of time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Beacon Temporary Removal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Beacon has been or will be temporarily removed from service.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Beacon Topmark Damaged
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The topmark of the beacon is damaged due to external factors (wind, sea state, collision with a vessel).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Beacon Topmark Missing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The topmark of the beacon is missing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Blasting Operation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An explosive detonation was observed at sea or blasting operation is scheduled to occur.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Breakwater Construction
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The construction of a structure protecting a shore area, harbour, or anchorage from waves.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bridge Horizontal Clearance Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The published horizontal clearance of the fixed or opening bridge has changed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bridge Unable To Close
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The functionality of an opening bridge is compromised. The bridge will remain open.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bridge Unable To Open
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The functionality of an opening bridge is compromised. The bridge will remain closed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Bridge Vertical Clearance Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The published vertical clearance of the fixed or opening bridge has changed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Adrift
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The buoy is no longer secured to its moorings and is adrift.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The characteristics of the buoy have been or will be changed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Commissioned for Navigation Season
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A buoy which was in ice over the winter and has been verified undamaged and in advertised position for the navigational season

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Damaged
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The buoy has been damaged due to external factors (wind, sea state, collision with a vessel).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Daymark Unreliable
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Colour of the buoy daymark is not visible due to damage or fading of colours (out of tolerance with colour recommendations).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Decommissioned for Winter
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A buoy which remains in the water over winter but which is declared unreliable (may be impacted by ice movement).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Destroyed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The buoy has suffered extensive damage and is not useable.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Establishment
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A new buoy has been or will be established.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Missing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: No buoy at its advertised/charted position or in the vicinity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Move
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The buoy has been or will be moved intentionally.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy off Position
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The buoy has been dragged off its advertised position due to wind or current affecting the mooring system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Re-established
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The re-establishment of a buoy which was previously announced either destroyed or temporarily removed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Removal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Buoy has been or will be permanently removed from service.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Replaced by Winter Spar
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A buoy which has been removed and it's location is now marked by a winter spar buoy.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Restored to Normal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The buoy has been restored to normal condition.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Temporary Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The characteristics of the buoy have been or will be temporarily changed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Temporary Establishment
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A new buoy has been or will be established for a limited period of time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Temporary Removal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Buoy has been or will be temporarily removed from service.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Topmark Damaged
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The topmark of the buoy is damaged due to external factors (wind, sea state, collision with a vessel).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Topmark Missing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The topmark of the buoy is missing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Will Be Withdrawn
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The buoy has been scheduled for removal from service for a fixed term.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Withdrawn
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The buoy has been removed from service for a fixed term.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Buoy Withdrawn for Winter
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A buoy has been withdrawn for the winter season.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cable Laying Operation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Operations being undertaken to lay wires, fibres, wire rope or chains underwater or to bury them beneath the sea floor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Cable Operations
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Underwater operations undertaken to maintain or repair a submarine cable.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Chayka Operating Properly
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The Chayka station is operating as advertised.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Chayka Out Of Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The Chayka station is inoperative due to a technical issue.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Chayka Station Removal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Chayka station has been or will be permanently removed from service.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: RAMARK Operating Properly
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The RAMARK is operating as advertised.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: RAMARK Out Of Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The RAMARK is inoperative.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: RAMARK removal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: RAMARK has been or will be permanently removed from service.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: RAMARK Temporary Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The characteristics of the RAMARK have been or will be temporarily changed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: RAMARK Temporary Establishment
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A new RAMARK has been or will be established for a limited period of time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: RAMARK Temporary Removal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: RAMARK has been or will be temporarily removed from service.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: RAMARK Unreliable
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The RAMARK is unreliable due to a technical issue or maintenance.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rear Beacon Restored to Normal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The rear leading beacon has been restored to normal condition. / The rear range beacon has been restored to normal condition.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rear Beacon Unreliable
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The rear leading beacon is damaged, obscured or missing. / The rear range beacon is damaged, obscured or missing

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rear Light is Operating Properly
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The rear leading light is operating as advertised. / The rear range light is operating as advertised.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rear Light Range Reduced
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The nominal range of the rear leading light is reduced. / The nominal range of the rear range light is reduced.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rear Light Unlit
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The rear leading light is extinguished. / The rear range light is extinguished.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rear Light Unreliable
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The operation of the rear leading light is unreliable due to technical problems. / The operation of the rear range light is unreliable due to technical problems.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rear Light Without Rhythm
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Due to technical problems, the rear leading light has no rhythm and is in fixed light mode. / Due to technical problems rear range light has no rhythm and is in fixed light mode.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Regatta or Race
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A short or long race of sail, oar or power craft along a predetermined course which may approach or cross navigation lanes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Renewable Energy Device or Farm Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The installation, removal, failure or damage of renewable energy devices (Wind turbines/farms, ocean current or wave power plants) which pose a hazard to safe navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Restricted Area Changes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A new or revised specified area, temporary or permanent in nature, designated by an appropriate authority within which navigation is restricted in accordance with certain specified conditions.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sandspit or Sandbar Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Significant changes to the limits or depth of a known sandbar/sandspit, or the discovery of a new sandbar/sandspit, which poses a hazard to safe navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: SAR Exercise
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A large scale activity where multiple vessels, surveillance aircraft, and shore-based personnel practice search and rescue techniques, in order to evaluate the effectiveness of response capability.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: SAR Operation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A real time response by vessels, surveillance aircraft, and shore-based personnel participating in an active search and rescue operation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Scientific Buoy Adrift
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A buoy fit for scientific purposes which has broken free of its moorings or has been left free and is adrift.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Scientific Moorings
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A submerged platform where a scientific instrument is secured and which may or may not be secured to the sea floor by means of an anchor chain.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Scientific Survey
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An activity where one or more vessels, restricted in their ability to manoeuvre, navigate along a pre-determine grid pattern in order to collect scientific data.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sea Trials
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Sea testing phase of a vessel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Seaplane Operations
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Activity within a defined area on the water where seaplanes are actively engaged in take-off, landing or taxiing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Seasonal Commissioning Complete
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The completion of the process to place summer buoys (and the removal of any winter spar buoys).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Seasonal Commissioning in Progress
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The commencement of the process to place summer buoys (and the removal of any winter spar buoys).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Seasonal Decommissioning Complete
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The completion of the process to remove summer buoys (and possibly replace some with winter spar buoys).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Seasonal Decommissioning in Progress
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The commencement of the process to remove summer buoys (and possibly replace some with winter spar buoys).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sector Light - Sector Obscured
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The light sector has been fully or partly obscured.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sector Light Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The characteristics of the sector light have been or will be changed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Sector Light Temporary Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The characteristics of the sector light have been or will be temporarily changed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Security Regulation Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Changes to the national, regional or port-specific maritime security regulations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Seismic Survey Operation
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The commencement or cessation of the complex operations of a seismic survey.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Shallow Depth Confirmed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Confirmed significant change to the depth or position of a charted sounding/shoal, or the discovery of a new shoal, which poses a hazard to safe navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Shallow Depth Reported
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Reported significant change to the depth or position of a charted sounding/shoal, or the discovery of a new shoal, which poses a hazard to safe navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spar Buoy Adrift
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The spar buoy is no longer secured to its moorings and has gone adrift from its advertised position.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spar Buoy Damaged
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The spar buoy has been damaged due to external factors (wind, sea state, collision with a vessel).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spar Buoy Destroyed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The spar buoy has suffered extensive damage and is not useable.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spar Buoy Missing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: No spar buoy at its advertised position or in the vicinity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spar Buoy Move
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The spar buoy has been or will be moved intentionally.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spar Buoy off Position
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The spar buoy has been dragged off its advertised position due to wind or current affecting the mooring system.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spar Buoy Re-established
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The re-establishment of a spar buoy which was previously announced either destroyed or temporarily removed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spar Buoy Restored to Normal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The spar buoy has been restored to normal condition.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spar Buoy Topmark Missing
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The topmark of the spar buoy is missing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Spar Buoy Withdrawn
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The spar buoy has been removed from service for a fixed term.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Storm Surge
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A rise above normal water level on the open coast due only to the action of wind stress on the water surface. Storm surge resulting from a hurricane or other intense storm also includes the rise in level due to atmospheric pressure reduction as well as that due to wind stress. A storm surge is more severe when it occurs in conjunction with a high tide. Also called storm tide, storm wave, tidal wave.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Submarine Cable Changes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Change in status, location or depth of a submerged or seabed cable which poses a hazard to safe navigation, anchoring or fishing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Submarine Pipeline Changes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Change in status, location or depth of a submerged or seabed pipeline which poses a hazard to safe navigation, anchoring or fishing.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Submerged Object
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any object under water; not showing above water.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Subsurface Mooring
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A mooring which is under water and which may or may not be secured to the sea floor by means of an anchor chain.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Swimmers
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A single person or groups of persons will be / are swimming in or near navigation lanes.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Temporary Buoyage
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The establishment of a buoy or group of buoys for a limited period of time (i.e. during summer season or during marine construction projects).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Tide Gauge Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The installation or removal of a tide gauge.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Traffic Congestion
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An area is experiencing a significantly high volume of vessel traffic which could potentially impede the progress of a vessel.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Tsunami Warning
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An alert message concerning strong waves, the widespread inundation of water, due to an earthquake, landslide or volcanic eruption, which is issued when the threat is imminent, expected or occurring.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Uncharted Rock
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A newly located rock, submerged or partially submerged rock, which had not been previously charted.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Underwater Operations
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Underwater work to maintain or repair subsurface structures (e.g. drill head).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unidentified Radar Target - Possible Iceberg
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An unidentified radar target, within the advertised limits of ice, but not yet visually confirmed as being an iceberg.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unwieldy Tow
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A tow, which by the nature of the size, shape or dimensions of the object being towed, is cumbersome to effectively tow regardless of the conditions of the waterway.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: V-AIS Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The characteristics of the V-AIS have been or will be changed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: V-AIS Establishment
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A new V-AIS has been or will be established.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: V-AIS Operating Properly
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Virtual AIS aid to navigation is operating as advertised.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: V-AIS Out Of Service
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Virtual AIS aid to navigation is extinguished.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: V-AIS Removal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: V-AIS has been or will be permanently removed from service.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: V-AIS Temporary Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The characteristics of the V-AIS have been or will be temporarily changed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: V-AIS Temporary Establishment
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A new V-AIS has been or will be established for a limited period of time.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: V-AIS Temporary Removal
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: V-AIS has been or will be temporarily removed from service.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: V-AIS Unreliable
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Virtual AIS aid is unreliable due to a technical issue or maintenance.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Vertical Clearance Reduced
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The reduction in the vertical distance between the air draft of a vessel and the lowest point on a bridge structure, cable or pipeline of which the vessel is intending to pass underneath.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Vessel Adrift
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A vessel at sea or which has lost mechanical capability and cannot be moored or anchored.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Vessel Disabled
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A vessel adrift at sea or safely anchored/moored, which has been damaged or has experienced some sort of mechanical or electrical failure so it can no longer sail.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: VHF Service Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any outage or return to operation of any VHF service (radiotelephone or digital selective calling).

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Volcano Activity
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Volcano activity impacting safe navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: VTS Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Change to an existing vessel traffic service zone limit, procedure and or provision of broadcast service relating to vessels operating within that zone.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Waterway Recommended or Not Recommended For Shipping
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Temporary or permanent changes to a waterway/fairway which may render it unsafe/safe for marine traffic.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Wharf Construction
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The commencement or cessation of wharf construction.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Works in Progress
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An active marine project, either on the surface or under water, which may affect the navigation of vessels.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: World Health Organization Notice
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Notice issued by World Health Organization to persons ashore or at sea.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Navwarn Type General
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: General type of a navigational warning or navigational hazard.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Aids to Navigation Changes
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any casualties to lights, fog signals, buoys and other aids to navigation affecting shipping; establishment of major new aids to navigation or significant changes to existing ones, when such establishment or change might be misleading to shipping.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Aquaculture and Fishing Installations
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: New or established aquaculture and fishing installations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Drifting Hazards
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Drifting hazards, including derelict ships, containers, other large items, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: ECDIS Operating Anomalies including Official Data Issues
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Operating anomalies identified within ECDIS, including issues with official data.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Other Hazards
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Hazards likely to constitute a danger to navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Health Advisories
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Health advisories or information.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Ice Information
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Newly discovered icebergs, changes to ice conditions and ice related information likely to impact navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: In-Force Bulletin
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A list of serial numbers of warnings which are in-force.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Dangerous Natural Phenomena
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Natural phenomena adversely affecting the marine environment.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Newly Discovered Dangers
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Newly discovered rocks, shoals, reefs and wrecks likely to constitute a danger to navigation and, if relevant, their markings.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Offshore Infrastructure
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: New or established complex structures situated at sea, including rigs, drilling platforms, offshore wind turbines, cables and pipelines.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Piracy or Robbery
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Acts of piracy and armed robbery against ships.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Communication or Broadcast Service Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Any failure or return to service of terrestrial or satellite radio services used to determine the position of an object.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Routeing Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Changes to the established navigational routes or specific procedures related to them.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Scientific Instruments Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Deployment or removal of scientific instruments on the surface, subsurface or on the sea floor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Security Requirement Change
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Changes to the maritime security levels in a country, a specific region or port. Or, changes to maritime security regulations.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Special Operations
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Events which might affect the safety of shipping, sometimes over wide areas, e.g. naval exercises, missile firings, space missions, nuclear tests, ordnance dumping zones, etc.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Towing Operations
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Objects being towed which are impacting navigation of vessels in its vicinity.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Works
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Works at sea or onshore which might affect navigation.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Rig List
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An update on the position, movement or status of rigs or drill ships within a defined area.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Uncertainty Fixed
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the fixed horizontal or vertical accuracy component for positions, depths, heights, vertical distances and vertical clearances.

S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:name: Quality of Horizontal Measurement
S100FC:S100_FC_SimpleAttribute.S100FC:definition: The degree of reliability attributed to a position.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Surveyed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The position(s) was(were) determined by the operation of making measurements for determining the relative position of points on, above or beneath the earth's surface. Survey implies a regular, controlled survey of any date.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unsurveyed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Survey data is does not exist or is very poor.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Inadequately Surveyed
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Not surveyed to modern standards; or due to its age, scale, or positional or vertical uncertainties is not suitable to the type of navigation expected in the area.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Approximate
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A position that is considered to be less than third-order accuracy, but is generally considered to be within 30.5 metres of its correct geographic location. Also may apply to a feature whose position does not remain fixed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Position Doubtful
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: Of uncertain position. The expression is used principally on charts to indicate that a wreck, shoal, etc., has been reported in various positions and not definitely determined in any.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Unreliable
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A feature's position has been obtained from questionable or unreliable data.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Reported (Not Surveyed)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An object whose position has been reported and its position confirmed by some means other than a formal survey such as an independent report of the same object.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Reported (Not Confirmed)
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: An object whose position has been reported and its position has not been confirmed.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Estimated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: The most probable position of an object determined from incomplete data or data of questionable accuracy.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Precisely Known
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A position that is of a known value, such as the position of an anchor berth or other defined object.

S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:label: Calculated
S100FC:listedValue.S100FC:definition: A position that is computed from data.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Affected Chart Publications
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Identifies paper charts, ENCs or publications that are affected by the information.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Chart Affected
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Name or number of affected national paper chart or ENC.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Fixed Date Range
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: An active period of a single fixed event or occurrence, as the date range between discrete start and end dates.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: Dates must be encoded in the format YYYYMMDD; using 4 digits for the calendar year (YYYY) and, optionally, 2 digits for the month (MM) (for example April = 04) and 2 digits for the day (DD). When no specific month and/or day is required/known, the values are replaced with dashes (-). The date range of a recurring event or occurrence must be encoded using periodicDateRange.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: General Area
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The general area used to identify which broad geographic region the message affects. The geographical name which is selected for the general area should be one that can be found on charts and in nautical publications. (S-53, 6).

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Information
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Textual information about the feature. The information may be provided as a string of text or as a file name of a single external text file that contains the text.
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:remarks: At least one of the sub-attributes file reference or text must be populated.The sub-attribute file reference is generally used for long text strings or those that require formatting, however, there is no restriction on the type of text (except for lexical level) that can be held in files referenced by sub-attribute file reference.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Locality
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Name and/or identifier of an area locality.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Location Name
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Name of an area locality as defined by a competent authority.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Message Series Identifier
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Message series identification of the warning or notice.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Feature Reference
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Reference to an object or feature that is external to the dataset.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Feature Name
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Provides the name of an entity, defines the national language of the name, and provides the option to display the name at various system display settings.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Horizontal Position Uncertainty
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: The best estimate of the accuracy of a position.

S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:name: Spatial Accuracy
S100FC:S100_FC_ComplexAttribute.S100FC:definition: Provides an indication of the vertical and horizontal positional uncertainty of bathymetric data, optionally within a specified date range.

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: header
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: The header of a navigational warning.

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: theWarningPart
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: The body of a navigational warning.

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: theReferences
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: The references relevant to the navigational warning

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: theWarning
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: The navigational warning that has references

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: thePositionProvider
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: A pointer to a specific feature(s).

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: theCartographicText
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: A pointer to a specific cartographically positioned location for text.

S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:name: impacts
S100FC:S100_FC_Role.S100FC:definition: marked by an area to show impacts

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationAssociation.S100FC:name: navwarnPreambleContent
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationAssociation.S100FC:definition: The binding between a navigational warning preamble and the body.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationAssociation.S100FC:name: navwarnReferences
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationAssociation.S100FC:definition: The relationship between a navigational warning and previous information relevant to its purpose.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureAssociation.S100FC:name: Text association
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureAssociation.S100FC:definition: a feature association for the binding between a geo feature and the cartographically positioned location for text.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureAssociation.S100FC:name: Area Affected
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureAssociation.S100FC:definition: Association between a warning and the area impacted.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: References
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: References to for example a navigational warning, nautical publication or chart.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: NAVWARN Preamble
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: Preamble information for warnings, notices and other types of messages in a navigational warning scheme.

S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:name: Spatial Quality
S100FC:S100_FC_InformationType.S100FC:definition: The indication of the quality of the locational information for features in a dataset.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: NAVWARN Part
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: Navigational warning information that may be geo-located.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: NAVWARN Area Affected
S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:definition: An area affected by some event marked by a navigational warning.

S100FC:S100_FC_FeatureType.S100FC:name: Text Placement
